<title>USA: Harris gets U.S. Navy contract.</title>
<headline>Harris gets U.S. Navy contract.</headline>
<dateline>MELBOURNE, Fla. 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Harris Corp said on Tuesday that it received a multi-million dollar contract to provide the U.S. Navy with a digital map system that improves navigation and situational awareness for aircraft.</p>
<p>McDonnell Douglas Corp selected Harris for the engineering, manufacture and development of the map system, Harris said. The contract has several follow-on production options, Harris said.</p>
<p>Harris is providing a similar modular map technology for the U.S. Air Force and U.S. Army Special Operations helicopter fleets, it said.</p>
